title: It Happened: Angus Young Joined GN'R Onstage Last Night, This Is What It Sounded Like [News]
text:
UG News editor since early 2013. King Crimson fan. I handle the news around here. Posted 9 hours ago 6 
The rumors turned out to be true as AC/DC guitar legend Angus Young joined Guns N' Roses onstage last night in Sydney for a rockin' performance of " Whole Lotta Rosie " and " Riff Raff ." 
What made the event a little bit more special is the fact that Angus performed without his trademark schoolboy outfit. 
"We're gonna bring out a friend of ours," Axl told the crowd. "Ladies and gentlemen, Angus Young! ... Here's something you never see. He didn't have his school uniform, but I'm wearing a school jacket." 
Fan-filmed footage was quick to surface, you can check it out in the embedded player below.
